1
00:00:10,844 --> 00:00:13,012
[Tahani] We're finally headed
to the Good Place.

2
00:00:13,096 --> 00:00:15,056
It's the "me" of places.

3
00:00:15,140 --> 00:00:18,101
I got in. I can say stuff like that again.

4
00:00:18,184 --> 00:00:20,311
Are you sure
we're going the right way, Janet?

5
00:00:20,395 --> 00:00:22,689
Well, I've never been
to the Good Place before.

6
00:00:23,189 --> 00:00:24,983
But, yes, I am sure.

7
00:00:25,650 --> 00:00:26,693
How?

8
00:00:26,776 --> 00:00:27,736
Because...

9
00:00:28,611 --> 00:00:30,739
it feels like I'm on my way home.

10
00:00:32,782 --> 00:00:34,284
[Jason] Flying puppy!

11
00:00:34,367 --> 00:00:36,870
You're almost there.
Just a little further.

12
00:00:36,953 --> 00:00:38,163
[Michael] Flying puppies?

13
00:00:38,246 --> 00:00:39,497
Dang it, Michael.

14
00:00:39,581 --> 00:00:41,458
Why didn't you think of that
for your neighborhood?

15
00:00:41,541 --> 00:00:43,501
These guys are good.

16
00:00:57,932 --> 00:01:01,019
[Tahani] I feel just like
Dorothy when she lands in Oz,

17
00:01:01,102 --> 00:01:03,855
{\an8}excited, incredulous,

18
00:01:03,938 --> 00:01:06,316
{\an8}much taller than everyone else around me.

19
00:01:06,399 --> 00:01:08,610
{\an8}What's everyone wanna do first?

20
00:01:08,693 --> 00:01:10,153
{\an8}Racing go-karts with monkeys.

21
00:01:10,236 --> 00:01:11,237
{\an8}Sure.

22
00:01:11,321 --> 00:01:13,323
{\an8}It's my lifelong dream.

23
00:01:13,406 --> 00:01:15,533
{\an8}Monkeys are the ideal go-kart opponents.

24
00:01:15,617 --> 00:01:18,870
{\an8}They're funny enough to give the finger,
but not smart enough to win.

25
00:01:20,914 --> 00:01:23,166
{\an8}-[Janet] Does that mean me?
-You're a Good Janet.

26
00:01:23,249 --> 00:01:25,835
{\an8}We're in the Good Place.
I don't know who else it would mean.

27
00:01:25,919 --> 00:01:27,670
{\an8}Okay. No pressure.

28
00:01:27,754 --> 00:01:29,631
{\an8}I was born to do this. Not born.

29
00:01:33,384 --> 00:01:34,385
{\an8}Okay.

30
00:01:34,469 --> 00:01:36,471
{\an8}So, I now know all the information
about the Good Place.

31
00:01:36,554 --> 00:01:38,515
{\an8}In a nutshell, it slaps.

32
00:01:38,598 --> 00:01:39,682
{\an8}First thing to tell you,

33
00:01:39,766 --> 00:01:43,978
{\an8}humans can't see the Good Place all at
once or their brains will be scrambled.

34
00:01:44,062 --> 00:01:47,774
{\an8}Cool. Maybe I'll finally get
some of those squigglies on my brain.

35
00:01:47,857 --> 00:01:50,110
{\an8}Doctors said my brain's
as smooth as an egg.

36
00:01:50,193 --> 00:01:52,487
{\an8}You all need to wait out here for a bit,
so you can adjust.

37
00:01:52,570 --> 00:01:55,156
{\an8}When you're ready,
you will be honored with a welcome gala,

38
00:01:55,240 --> 00:01:58,660
{\an8}magically planned by the Good Place,
based on your personalities.

39
00:01:58,743 --> 00:02:01,996
{\an8}Like the targeted Instagram ad of parties.

40
00:02:02,080 --> 00:02:04,958
{\an8}You know, I bought the coolest sunglasses
from one of those ads.

41
00:02:05,041 --> 00:02:05,875
Look.

42
00:02:06,709 --> 00:02:07,877
-[Jason] Whoa!
-[gasps]

43
00:02:08,336 --> 00:02:10,171
-It's like I'm inside the Internet.
-[Tahani and Chidi chuckle]

44
00:02:10,839 --> 00:02:11,673
[Michael] Okay.

45
00:02:11,756 --> 00:02:12,632
Could we just keep moving?

46
00:02:12,715 --> 00:02:13,883
You look a little pale.

47
00:02:13,967 --> 00:02:15,343
Did you get sick from the hot air balloon?

48
00:02:15,426 --> 00:02:17,262
I bet if you throw up
it'll just be butterflies or something.

49
00:02:17,345 --> 00:02:18,221
[Michael] I'm fine.

50
00:02:18,304 --> 00:02:19,347
I just, um...

51
00:02:20,557 --> 00:02:21,766
I don't belong here.

52
00:02:21,850 --> 00:02:25,436
There's no telling what will happen
to a demon who steps foot in this place.

53
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:28,565
Promise me, if I'm vaporized,
you guys just keep having fun.

54
00:02:28,648 --> 00:02:29,566
[bell chimes]

55
00:02:29,649 --> 00:02:32,652
Oh, my goodness,
that chime is so soothing.

56
00:02:32,735 --> 00:02:34,863
Feels like my brain is being massaged...

57
00:02:34,946 --> 00:02:36,447
-[Tahani and Chidi] ...by a baby deer.
-[Michael] Oh, boy.

58
00:02:36,531 --> 00:02:39,576
What if that's some sort of demon alarm,
to alert the cops that I'm here?

59
00:02:39,659 --> 00:02:42,162
-You want me to hold your weed?
-I don't have weed.

60
00:02:43,496 --> 00:02:44,330
Oh...

61
00:02:44,998 --> 00:02:45,832
Wait a minute.

62
00:02:45,915 --> 00:02:47,750
Oh, yeah, okay, now, I do.

63
00:02:47,834 --> 00:02:48,918
Take this.

64
00:02:49,002 --> 00:02:50,295
[Janet] They're ready
for you to move inside.

65
00:02:50,378 --> 00:02:52,005
The Good Place Committee
is waiting for us.

66
00:02:54,340 --> 00:02:57,468
{\an8}[Eleanor] Oh, man, look at this place.

67
00:02:58,303 --> 00:03:01,055
{\an8}Karlie Kloss did like me.

68
00:03:01,139 --> 00:03:02,181
{\an8}I knew it.

69
00:03:02,265 --> 00:03:03,641
{\an8}-So, about this party...
-[Janet] Yeah.

70
00:03:03,725 --> 00:03:05,226
{\an8}Is everyone in the Good Place invited?

71
00:03:05,310 --> 00:03:07,020
{\an8}Like, is Aristotle going to be there?

72
00:03:07,103 --> 00:03:10,607
Sorry, Chidi, Aristotle's in
the Bad Place. He defended slavery.

73
00:03:10,690 --> 00:03:12,066
-Socrates?
-[Janet] No.

74
00:03:12,150 --> 00:03:13,735
Too annoying. Very loud chewer.

75
00:03:13,818 --> 00:03:15,653
-Plato?
-Slavery again.

76
00:03:15,737 --> 00:03:16,946
Ooh, you know who is here?

77
00:03:17,030 --> 00:03:19,657
Hypatia of Alexandria. Do you know her?

78
00:03:19,741 --> 00:03:20,867
Hypatia?

79
00:03:21,492 --> 00:03:23,077
-Of Alexandria?
-That's right.

80
00:03:23,161 --> 00:03:25,330
Uh, yeah, I know her.

81
00:03:25,413 --> 00:03:26,873
[muffled screaming]

82
00:03:27,498 --> 00:03:29,834
Hypatia. I'm gonna ask her
so many questions

83
00:03:29,918 --> 00:03:31,711
pertaining to grand ideas
about the universe.

84
00:03:31,794 --> 00:03:32,670
Like... "Why?"

85
00:03:32,754 --> 00:03:36,007
Oh, oh, and also... "How?"

86
00:03:36,090 --> 00:03:37,050
Ooh!

87
00:03:37,133 --> 00:03:38,801
Welcome to the Good Place, everyone.

88
00:03:38,885 --> 00:03:40,595
[Drew] Michael, so happy you made it.

89
00:03:40,678 --> 00:03:41,971
You look radiant.

90
00:03:42,055 --> 00:03:45,642
You have the calming yet authoritative
presence of a bomb-sniffing dog.

91
00:03:45,725 --> 00:03:47,018
I'd just like to say

92
00:03:47,101 --> 00:03:50,146
thank you so much
for letting me be here with my friends.

93
00:03:50,230 --> 00:03:53,107
I know it's unorthodox
for someone like myself

94
00:03:53,191 --> 00:03:55,735
to visit the Good Place,
but it's just so wonderful.

95
00:03:55,818 --> 00:03:58,821
And I don't have any weed on me,
so no need for the cops. [laughs]

96
00:03:58,905 --> 00:04:01,491
Michael, Michael,
you and your friends are heroes,

97
00:04:01,574 --> 00:04:03,409
and you're more than welcome here.

98
00:04:03,493 --> 00:04:05,578
In fact, we have some very exciting news.

99
00:04:05,662 --> 00:04:07,372
While the rest of you get settled in,

100
00:04:07,455 --> 00:04:09,791
we wanna give Michael
a swearing-in ceremony,

101
00:04:09,874 --> 00:04:12,210
so he can become
an official Good Place architect.

102
00:04:13,586 --> 00:04:14,462
[Eleanor gasps]

103
00:04:14,545 --> 00:04:16,047
Oh, my goodness.

104
00:04:16,130 --> 00:04:17,632
Michael, please, follow us.

105
00:04:18,299 --> 00:04:19,550
[bell chimes]

106
00:04:19,634 --> 00:04:23,012
Holy fork, that is a soothing chime.

107
00:04:23,096 --> 00:04:26,683
It really is the most incredible chime
I've ever heard.

108
00:04:26,766 --> 00:04:28,434
And that is coming
from someone whose godfather

109
00:04:28,518 --> 00:04:30,395
is the most famous clock in the world.

110
00:04:30,478 --> 00:04:35,024
-Is Big Ben somehow your godfather?
-Mmm-hmm.

111
00:04:35,108 --> 00:04:36,359
That sound means...

112
00:04:36,943 --> 00:04:38,278
it's party time.

113
00:04:41,155 --> 00:04:43,491
When you walk through,
the event space will transform

114
00:04:43,574 --> 00:04:47,036
into a party perfectly tailored
to your essences.

115
00:04:47,620 --> 00:04:50,248
Let's link arms and walk through together.

116
00:04:58,464 --> 00:04:59,382
Weird.

117
00:04:59,465 --> 00:05:00,383
[Jason] Whoa!

118
00:05:00,466 --> 00:05:04,262
This is the Jacksonville SuperSuites
hotel ballroom where I had my prom

119
00:05:04,345 --> 00:05:05,513
and also traffic court.

120
00:05:06,055 --> 00:05:08,182
But this has to be my party,

121
00:05:08,266 --> 00:05:12,186
because that's the bedpan
that Stone Cold Steve Austin

122
00:05:12,270 --> 00:05:16,399
used to beat up Vince McMahon
in 1998. [gasps]

123
00:05:16,899 --> 00:05:19,068
It was a classic moment. Don't judge me.

124
00:05:19,152 --> 00:05:20,403
I'm so sorry, guys.

125
00:05:20,486 --> 00:05:24,157
The Good Place uses your life experiences
to plan the perfect party,

126
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:26,367
but it's only designed
for one person at a time.

127
00:05:26,451 --> 00:05:28,244
When you walked in as a group,
it became...

128
00:05:28,328 --> 00:05:30,330
A mish-mash of all four of us.

129
00:05:35,084 --> 00:05:36,044
[sighs contentedly]

130
00:05:36,502 --> 00:05:37,795
It's perfect.

131
00:05:38,379 --> 00:05:40,715
Um, no, it's not, Eleanor,

132
00:05:40,798 --> 00:05:43,342
because there's no go-kart track,
and no monkeys.

133
00:05:43,426 --> 00:05:45,178
No offense, but you're being
a real smooth-brain right now.

134
00:05:45,261 --> 00:05:46,345
See those green doors?

135
00:05:46,429 --> 00:05:50,767
You can use them to visit
any time or place, real or imagined.

136
00:05:50,850 --> 00:05:52,310
Just think about where you wanna go,

137
00:05:52,393 --> 00:05:55,104
and what you wanna do,
and walk on through.

138
00:05:55,188 --> 00:05:56,606
So, one could walk amongst the dinosaurs,

139
00:05:56,689 --> 00:06:00,443
or witness the very first production of
<i>Hamlet</i> at the Globe Theater.

140
00:06:00,526 --> 00:06:03,821
I'mma go Tokyo Drift with monkeys.
See you in a thousand years.

141
00:06:05,281 --> 00:06:06,991
Do you mind if I go find Hypatia?

142
00:06:07,075 --> 00:06:08,910
I promise it's strictly platonic.

143
00:06:08,993 --> 00:06:12,080
-Technically, Neoplatonic. [laughs]
-Whoops.

144
00:06:12,163 --> 00:06:15,666
Forget I made that joke and come with me.
I'm so nervous to meet her.

145
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:18,419
I need someone cool there to change
the subject if I say something dumb.

146
00:06:18,503 --> 00:06:19,712
Sure. Gimme one sec.

147
00:06:19,796 --> 00:06:22,090
Hey, Tahani, this room is filled

148
00:06:22,173 --> 00:06:25,051
with some of the most interesting people
that ever lived.

149
00:06:25,134 --> 00:06:27,220
Chat them up, learn about their lives,

150
00:06:27,303 --> 00:06:30,723
then meet back here
so that we can make fun of them.

151
00:06:31,390 --> 00:06:36,062
Eleanor Shellstrop, I have been training
for this day my entire life.

152
00:06:37,396 --> 00:06:40,024
I'm so honored by this gesture.

153
00:06:40,108 --> 00:06:43,069
This feels right.
This will be my new purpose.

154
00:06:43,152 --> 00:06:44,904
Everything's falling into place.

155
00:06:44,987 --> 00:06:48,074
Great. Let's get to it.
Just put on this ceremonial robe.

156
00:06:48,157 --> 00:06:49,033
[Michael chuckles]

157
00:06:49,117 --> 00:06:51,953
[Drew] Boy, do you have
the shoulders for a robe.

158
00:06:52,036 --> 00:06:53,955
-Oh.
-Just sign this scroll.

159
00:06:54,622 --> 00:06:56,958
I've never signed my name before.

160
00:06:57,583 --> 00:07:00,128
What signature type to choose?

161
00:07:00,211 --> 00:07:01,921
"Doctor Blob." Or, no...

162
00:07:02,004 --> 00:07:04,340
"Athlete who doesn't really care
about the kid."

163
00:07:04,966 --> 00:07:05,842
Oh, wait, no...

164
00:07:05,925 --> 00:07:08,719
"Middle school girl
with crush on Zac Efron."

165
00:07:08,803 --> 00:07:13,933
That way,
I can put a little heart over the "I."

166
00:07:14,016 --> 00:07:17,311
Perfect. And here is your official medal.

167
00:07:17,395 --> 00:07:19,730
Now I know what
Mary Lou Retton feels like.

168
00:07:19,814 --> 00:07:20,648
And great.

169
00:07:20,731 --> 00:07:22,942
Now, you are officially
in charge of the Good Place.

170
00:07:23,025 --> 00:07:25,820
-I'm sorry, "in charge"?
-Yup. You're the boss now.

171
00:07:25,903 --> 00:07:29,532
That was all legally binding,
and we all quit, effective immediately.

172
00:07:29,615 --> 00:07:32,243
That is irreversible,
so it's all your problem now.

173
00:07:32,326 --> 00:07:34,954
Don't try to find us.
No take-backs, okay, bye-bye!

174
00:07:35,037 --> 00:07:36,873
Hurry, move, move! Go, go, go!

175
00:07:41,919 --> 00:07:44,881
Hello? Fellow Good Placemen?

176
00:07:46,757 --> 00:07:47,717
Anyone in here?

177
00:07:49,093 --> 00:07:51,554
"Ideas for improving the Good Place." Oh.

178
00:07:51,637 --> 00:07:53,306
"Music you can eat."

179
00:07:53,389 --> 00:07:54,348
Oh, boy.

180
00:07:54,432 --> 00:07:58,603
"Giant mini-donuts,
not just regular donuts.

181
00:07:58,686 --> 00:08:00,104
Dave will explain."

182
00:08:01,022 --> 00:08:04,275
Dave? Can you explain?

183
00:08:04,984 --> 00:08:10,114
Um, hi, are you...
are you Hypatia of Alexandria?

184
00:08:10,198 --> 00:08:12,033
Yep. How's it hangin'?

185
00:08:12,116 --> 00:08:13,784
It's hangin' really well.

186
00:08:14,368 --> 00:08:19,624
Um, I gotta say, I was expecting you
to be, still, you know... ancient Greek.

187
00:08:19,707 --> 00:08:22,585
Oh! Well, no, we sort of stay current
in this place.

188
00:08:22,668 --> 00:08:24,837
What are the big things
from Earth recently?

189
00:08:24,921 --> 00:08:29,509
Um, the Industrial Revolution,
Manhattan Project, "Gangnam Style..."

190
00:08:29,592 --> 00:08:30,510
I feel like I get it.

191
00:08:30,593 --> 00:08:31,802
-It's really her!
-Yeah.

192
00:08:31,886 --> 00:08:34,680
I can just tell, somehow.
It's Hypatia of Alexandria.

193
00:08:34,764 --> 00:08:36,807
I know, babe. Yes, it is.

194
00:08:36,891 --> 00:08:40,394
Hi, sorry, I'm Eleanor.
This exuberant weirdo is Chidi.

195
00:08:40,478 --> 00:08:41,604
We're new in town.

196
00:08:41,687 --> 00:08:43,940
First question,
how do you get the "of" in your name?

197
00:08:44,023 --> 00:08:46,734
Is it where you hung out the most?

198
00:08:46,817 --> 00:08:50,738
Am I Eleanor of
the Cheesecake Factory Bar?

199
00:08:50,821 --> 00:08:53,991
Also, is it "Hy-pay-sha" or "Hy-pat-ia"?

200
00:08:54,075 --> 00:08:58,412
Or in the ancient Greek, "Who-put-tia"?
There's a lot of fun debate about this.

201
00:08:58,496 --> 00:08:59,956
You know what? Just call me Patty.

202
00:09:01,165 --> 00:09:05,711
Okay. Well, Patty, I'm a huge fan.

203
00:09:05,795 --> 00:09:08,589
I had a poster of you
on my wall in high school.

204
00:09:08,673 --> 00:09:11,592
Actually, it was just
a poster of Trinity from <i>The Matrix.</i>

205
00:09:11,676 --> 00:09:13,761
But that's how I imagined you would look.
Because you're so cool.

206
00:09:13,844 --> 00:09:16,138
Is she the reason you got beat up so much?

207
00:09:16,222 --> 00:09:17,265
She's one of them!

208
00:09:17,348 --> 00:09:18,724
Wanna get a milkshake?

209
00:09:18,808 --> 00:09:21,519
I haven't been around newbies in a while.
You're a little intense.

210
00:09:21,602 --> 00:09:23,396
Let's get a milkshake. Yeah.

211
00:09:23,479 --> 00:09:26,524
They make a milkshake here
that's made out of actual stardust.

212
00:09:26,607 --> 00:09:27,525
It's pretty good.

213
00:09:27,608 --> 00:09:30,987
Okay. Yeah. Getting milkshakes with Patty.

214
00:09:31,070 --> 00:09:31,988
Yeah. [chuckles]

215
00:09:32,071 --> 00:09:33,406
But can I ask you some questions first?

216
00:09:33,489 --> 00:09:36,075
You were a follower of Plotinus,

217
00:09:36,158 --> 00:09:38,452
who claimed that
contemplation of our ultimate reality--

218
00:09:38,536 --> 00:09:40,997
Wait, wait, wait, are you...

219
00:09:41,998 --> 00:09:45,918
What's it called, a think-book-man? Um...

220
00:09:46,544 --> 00:09:48,170
A think-read-book-man?

221
00:09:48,254 --> 00:09:49,255
A philosopher? Yes.

222
00:09:49,338 --> 00:09:52,758
Sorry, it's been so long,
my brain is foggy.

223
00:09:52,842 --> 00:09:56,721
Listen carefully
before I forget how to say this.

224
00:09:56,804 --> 00:10:00,099
You gotta help us. We are so screwed.

225
00:10:01,517 --> 00:10:02,602
We are?

226
00:10:03,936 --> 00:10:06,772
Hello! I'm Tahani Al-Jamil.

227
00:10:06,856 --> 00:10:09,567
I'm Paltibaal. Welcome to paradise.

228
00:10:09,650 --> 00:10:11,402
So, what's your story?

229
00:10:11,485 --> 00:10:14,530
Did you cure something?
Or invent something?

230
00:10:14,614 --> 00:10:16,949
I helped the poor in ancient Phoenicia.

231
00:10:17,033 --> 00:10:18,618
Excellent.

232
00:10:18,701 --> 00:10:21,078
I once had a SoulCycle instructor
named Phoenicia.

233
00:10:24,081 --> 00:10:25,374
How did you die?

234
00:10:25,458 --> 00:10:27,543
I got a cut on my hand.

235
00:10:28,127 --> 00:10:31,756
The year was 2491 BC,
so that's pretty much all it took.

236
00:10:31,839 --> 00:10:32,798
You got a cut

237
00:10:32,882 --> 00:10:36,344
or you drank water that wasn't hot enough,
and then, boom, dead.

238
00:10:37,219 --> 00:10:39,013
I would've killed for a vaccine.

239
00:10:39,096 --> 00:10:40,056
Any vaccine.

240
00:10:40,139 --> 00:10:43,601
It's crazy that you guys
just don't like them now.

241
00:10:43,684 --> 00:10:46,896
So, what's your favorite part
about living here?

242
00:10:46,979 --> 00:10:48,689
